{"lemma":"خاضِعُو","slug":"خاضِعُو","root":"خ.ض.ع","root_slug":"خ-ض-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ض-ع","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خاضِع","root":"خضع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n10913"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B6%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"submissive, subordinate, controlled (by)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of خَضَعَ (ḵaḍaʕa, “to submit”)."},"ipa":["/xaː.dˤiʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10913","headword_ar":"خَاضِعٌ","root":"xDE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDuwEN","text_ar":"خَضُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (S, K:) [or rather the latter is an intensive epithet, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very lowly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] the pl. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaADiEuwna","text_ar":"خَاضِعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuD~aEN","text_ar":"خُضَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDoEaAnN","text_ar":"خُضْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiDoEaAnN","text_ar":"خِضْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [respecting the last two of which, see 1, second sentence:] and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDuwEN","text_ar":"خَضُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDuEN","text_ar":"خُضُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN xuDuEu Alr~iqaAbi","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ خُضُعُ الرِّقَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men, very submissive in the necks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) It is said in the Kur [xxvi. 3],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZal~ato A^aEonaAquhumo","text_ar":"فَظَلَّتْ اَعْنَاقُهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahaA xaADiEiyna","text_ar":"لَهَا خَاضِعِينَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And their necks shall continue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the pret. being used in the sense of the aor., meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taduwmu","text_ar":"تَدُومُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Jel,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive to it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel, * TA:) the original of the phrase is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZal~uwA lahaA xaADiEiyna","text_ar":"فَظَلُّوا لَهَا خَاضِعِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEnAq","text_ar":"اعناق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is redundantly inserted to show the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDuwE","text_ar":"خُضُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the predicate is left in its original state: (Bd:) or as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xDwE","text_ar":"خضوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is only that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEnAq","text_ar":"اعناق"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is allowable to make the predicate relate to [the pronoun"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hm","text_ar":"هم"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is] the complement of the latter word: (Sb, Kh:) or since the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xDwE","text_ar":"خضوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ascribed to the necks but really belongs to the persons, the epithet has that form of pl. which is proper to rational beings: (Jel: [and the like is said by Bd:]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEnAqhm","text_ar":"اعناقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their chiefs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their companies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but there is another reading [which is literally grammatical], namely"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaADiEapF","text_ar":"خَاضِعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd.) ―         -b2-  The pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuD~aEN","text_ar":"خُضَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to Women"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who have been"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or who are"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft in speech, and still."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.) [See 1.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEaAmN xawaADiEu","text_ar":"نَعَامٌ خَوَاضِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaADiEapN","text_ar":"خَاضِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ostriches inclining their heads towards the ground in their places of pasture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZibaA='N","text_ar":"ظِبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gazelles"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilN xawaADiEu","text_ar":"اـِبِلٌ خَوَاضِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Camels striving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerting themselves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hastening, in their pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because, when they do so, they lower their necks. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokibN xaADiEN","text_ar":"مَنْكِبٌ خَاضِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaEu","text_ar":"اَخْضَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed, shoulder-joint."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nujuwmN xawaADiEu","text_ar":"نُجُومٌ خَوَاضِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stars inclining to setting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to their places of setting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inviting to that which is foul, abominable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Jel","Bd","Sb","Kh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}